{"_id":"class-druid","name":"Druid","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/oak.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Druids draw power from nature and the wild. They cast divine spells, gain an animal companion, and can assume animal and eventually elemental forms through wild shape.</p><h3>Alignment</h3><p>Any neutral (neutral good, lawful neutral, neutral, chaotic neutral, or neutral evil).</p><h3>Key Class Features</h3><ul><li><strong>Animal Companion:</strong> Loyal companion from a defined list; gains bonus HD, natural armor, and special abilities as the druid advances.</li><li><strong>Wild Shape:</strong> Transform into Small/Medium animals (5th), more uses and Large/Tiny/Huge over levels, plant form (12th), elemental form (16th).</li><li><strong>Spells:</strong> Prepare and cast divine spells from the druid list. Can spontaneously convert prepared spells to summon nature's ally.</li><li><strong>Nature Sense:</strong> +2 on Knowledge (nature) and Survival checks.</li><li><strong>Woodland Stride (2nd), Trackless Step (3rd), Resist Nature's Lure (4th), Venom Immunity (9th), Timeless Body (15th).</strong></li></ul><p><em>Ex-druids:</em> Ceasing to revere nature, changing to a prohibited alignment, or teaching Druidic to a non-druid loses all spells and druid abilities until atonement.</p>","hitDie":"d8","babProgression":"average","saves":{"fort":"good","ref":"poor","will":"good"},"skillPointsPerLevel":4,"classSkills":[{"key":"concentration","name":"Concentration"},{"key":"craft-alchemy","name":"Craft (Alchemy)"},{"key":"craft-armorsmithing","name":"Craft (Armorsmithing)"},{"key":"craft-bowmaking","name":"Craft (Bowmaking)"},{"key":"craft-weaponsmithing","name":"Craft (Weaponsmithing)"},{"key":"craft-trapmaking","name":"Craft (Trapsmithing)"},{"key":"diplomacy","name":"Diplomacy"},{"key":"handleAnimal","name":"Handle Animal"},{"key":"heal","name":"Heal"},{"key":"knowledge-nature","name":"Knowledge (Nature)"},{"key":"listen","name":"Listen"},{"key":"profession","name":"Profess